<recipe>
<title>
Lighter Cheesy Broccoli-Rice Casserole
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
16 oz . package of frozen broccoli , chopped
1 tsp . butter
1/2 c . onion , minced
1/2 c . fat-free Greek yogurt
1 (16 oz.) container low-fat cottage cheese
1 (10 oz.) can 98% fat- free cream of mushroom soup
2 c . shredded 2% sharp cheddar , divided
1 tsp . of Cajun seasoning
1/2 tsp . of garlic powder
1/2 tsp . black pepper
2 c . rice , cooked
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 13x9 inch baking dish.
Place broccoli in a microwave safe bowl, add about 1 tablespoon of water, cover and microwave about 6 to 8 minutes. Drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a skillet. Sauté the onion over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes.
In a larger bowl, stir together the Greek yogurt, cottage cheese, soup, 1 1/2 cups cheese, Cajun seasoning, garlic powder, and black pepper. Mix until well blended.
Add the sautéed onion, rice, and chopped broccoli to yogurt mixture. Stir gently until combined.
Pour out into the prepared baking dish. Cover with foil and bake for 20-25 minutes.
Remove the foil, sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese and return to the oven uncovered, for about 5 minutes or until cheese has melted.
</instructions>
</recipe>
